== Introduction ==

[http://redhat.com/spacewalk/ Spacewalk] is an open source Linux and Solaris systems management solution.  It allows you to:

  * Inventory your systems (hardware and software information)
  * Install and update software on your systems
  * Collect and distribute your custom software packages into manageable groups
  * Provision (Kickstart) your systems
  * Manage and deploy configuration files to your systems
  * Monitor your systems
  * Provision virtual guests
  * Start/stop/configure virtual guests

Spacewalk is the upstream project for the source of [http://www.redhat.com/red_hat_network/ Red Hat Network Satellite]. Spacewalk works with RHEL, Fedora, and other RHEL derivative distributions like CentOS, Scientific Linux, etc. We are working on getting it packaged
for inclusion in Fedora.

This wiki is primarily focused on the usage and development of Spacewalk. For a higher-level overview of Spacewalk, what it does, and for a full gallery of screenshots, please visit the [http://redhat.com/spacewalk Spacewalk website at redhat.com].

